To stream a URL from a .pls file using Java, you can use the Java Media Framework (JMF) to create a player and load the URL into it. Here's an example code snippet that demonstrates how to do this:

<<<api>>>: java.io.InputStream.read
<<<code>>>: InputStream inputStream = new FileInputStream("path/to/playlist.pls");
InputStreamReader inputStreamReader = new InputStreamReader(inputStream);
BufferedReader bufferedReader = new BufferedReader(inputStreamReader);
String line;
while ((line = bufferedReader.readLine()) != null) {
String url = line.trim();
if (url.startsWith("http")) {
Player player = Manager.createPlayer(new URL(url));
player.start();
}
}
<<<explanation>>>: This code reads the .pls file line by line and checks if each line starts with "http". If it does, it creates a player using the URL and starts playing it.

